sentences.english: It was immediately put to a severe test.
sentences.chinese: 它甫一问世便经历严峻考验。

sentences.english: And a year later, The Language of Baklava was published.
sentences.chinese: 一年之后《巴克拉瓦的语言》问世。

sentences.english: Recently theories of multiple modernities have emphasized the multiple features of modernity.
sentences.chinese: 多元现代性“理论问世后开始强调现代性的多种形式。

sentences.english: In 1995, the first foreign version of National Geographic magazine was unveiled.
sentences.chinese: 1995年，国家地理杂志第一个外文版问世。

sentences.english: A final version is expected in early 2005, according to the company.
sentences.chinese: 据微软透露，最终正式版将于2005初问世。

sentences.english: His masterpiece, The Way of All Flesh did not get much attention when it was firstly published.
sentences.chinese: 该作品在问世之初并没有引起世人太多的关注。

sentences.english: With it the new film has a chance to come to life.
sentences.chinese: 随着旧电影的腐烂，新电影将有机会得以问世。

sentences.english: Lately , a new type of sterilizer has appeared on the market.
sentences.chinese: 最近，一种新型的灭菌器问世了。

sentences.english: And as each invention arrives, it eats further into our time.
sentences.chinese: 而每一项新发明问世，就进一步吞噬我们的光阴。

sentences.english: Some research on Wang Chuanshan' s thought of nature and practice has been pub.
sentences.chinese: 有关王船山性习思想的研究，已有一些成果问世。

sentences.english: Shanghai General Motor announced the advent of its new "Sail".
sentences.chinese: 上海通用宣布其新产品“赛欧”轿车问世。

sentences.english: X-Rite's first colorimeter was also introduced in 1989.
sentences.chinese: 爱色丽的第一台色度仪也于1989年问世。

sentences.english: World's first camel-milk chocolates going global.
sentences.chinese: 世界首个骆驼奶巧克力在阿联酋问世。

sentences.english: Into Danish, too, it was translated shortly after its appearance.
sentences.chinese: 丹麦文译本也是在原书问世后不久就出版了。

sentences.english: A new model will come out this summer.
sentences.chinese: 往年炎天将有新的型号问世。

sentences.english: Air Travel: The first jet airliner, the Boeing 707, was introduced in 1959.
sentences.chinese: 1959年，波音707，第一架喷气式飞机问世。

definition: to be published (of art, literary works etc)/to come out/to take shape/to see the light of day
to hit the market (of a new product)
to push out/to release/to launch/to publish/to recommend
to put sth on the market
to confess one's crime/first model, version, kind etc (of gadgets, software, cars etc)
to emerge to meet a historic destiny (idiom)/to arise at an opportune time/able to take advantage of an opportunity/to rise to the occasion
to sell strongly/to be in great demand
to be popular for a while/to be all the rage for a time
